text: Dorinda Fraser (1947-2010), was a female swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== She represented England and won a bronze medal in 110 yards breaststroke, at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Perth, Western Australia. ==References== Category:1947 births Category:2010 deaths Category:English female swimmers Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Swimmers at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in swimming
